From: Oliver Lantwin <oliver@lantwin.de>
Subject: Namespace install destinations to avoid shared-prefix collisions

Upstream installs CMake modules, helper scripts, config-file fragment
templates, generated compat plugin builders, the catch2 main source, the
UPS templates and the LICENSE/README/INSTALL pkgmeta files to generic
top-level destinations (Modules/, bin/, src/, ups-templates/, the prefix
root, ...). On a shared prefix (conda env, /usr/local) these collide with
files shipped by other packages.

Namespace the architecture-independent ones under share/cetmodules/, move
the internal make_bash_completions helper under libexec, and suppress the
auto-installed pkgmeta docs:
  Modules/*.cmake               -> share/cetmodules/Modules/
  Modules/compat[-aux]/*        -> share/cetmodules/Modules/compat[-aux]/
  generated compat plugin dir   -> share/cetmodules/Modules/compat/art/
  bin/make_bash_completions     -> ${CMAKE_INSTALL_LIBEXECDIR} (libexec/cetmodules/)
  src/cet_catch2_main.cpp       -> share/cetmodules/src/  (CATCH2_MAIN PV updated to match)
  ups-templates/*               -> share/cetmodules/ups-templates/
  cet_cmake_env()               -> cet_cmake_env(NO_INSTALL_PKGMETA)

Because make_bash_completions moves to libexec, cet_make_completions() (used
by downstream consumers e.g. fhiclcpp's fhicl-expand) must invoke it from
LIBEXEC_DIR rather than BIN_DIR -- otherwise the generated *_completions
target depends on a nonexistent ${prefix}/bin/make_bash_completions and the
downstream build fails. CetMakeCompletions.cmake is updated accordingly.

The ETC_DIR / TOOLS_DIR project variables and the generated CMake config
output dir (CONFIG_OUTPUT_ROOT_DIR) are likewise pointed under share/cetmodules
via -D flags in build.sh rather than patched here. CONFIG_DIR (the config-file
fragment templates) is intentionally NOT relocated: cetmodules consumes that
variable at build time to locate its own CetConfigVersion templates (via
cet_localize_pv against the source/binary tree), so overriding its value breaks
the self-build; it stays at the top-level config/.

The internal libexec helpers (checkClassVersion, filter-program-options, ...)
already install under ${cetmodules_LIBEXEC_DIR}, which build.sh points at
libexec/cetmodules via -DCMAKE_INSTALL_LIBEXECDIR, so they need no change.

Downstream find_package(cetmodules) consumers are unaffected otherwise: paths
registered with cet_cmake_module_directories() and the localized CATCH2_MAIN
project variable follow these relocations, and the compat plugin builders keep
their relative position under the Modules root.

make_bash_completions previously located its companion filter-program-options
via "${BASH_SOURCE%/*}/../libexec"; once it lives in libexec/cetmodules/
alongside that companion the relative path is just the script's own directory.

In 3.24.01 (vs 4.x) make_bash_completions is bundled with the other public
scripts in a single cet_script() call, so it is split out into its own
cet_script() with an explicit libexec DESTINATION.

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 1c26e4a..bb64276 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -53,7 +53,10 @@ cet_set_version_from_file(EXTENDED_VERSION_SEMANTICS)
 ####################################
 # Basic build environment.
 include(CetCMakeEnv)
-cet_cmake_env()
+# NO_INSTALL_PKGMETA: don't auto-install INSTALL/LICENSE/README to the prefix
+# root (they collide on a shared conda prefix; the LICENSE is captured via the
+# recipe's about.license_file instead).
+cet_cmake_env(NO_INSTALL_PKGMETA)
 
 project_variable(MIN_CETBUILDTOOLS_VERSION 8.04.00 TYPE STRING CONFIG
   DOCSTRING "Minimum version of cetbuildtools compatible with this version---${cetmodules_VERSION}---of cetmodules")
@@ -66,7 +69,7 @@ project_variable(MIN_CMAKE_VERSION TYPE STRING CONFIG
   DOCSTRING "Minimum version of CMake compatible with this version---${cetmodules_VERSION}---of cetmodules")
 
 # Make sure downstream packages can find our modules.
-cet_cmake_module_directories(NO_LOCAL Modules Modules/compat)
+cet_cmake_module_directories(NO_LOCAL share/cetmodules/Modules share/cetmodules/Modules/compat)
 
 ####################################
 # Build components.
